==English==
===Etymology===
Compound of ''[[be-]]'' and the verb ''[[ware]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛə(r)|-ɛə(r)]]

===Verb===
'''to beware'''

# (''defective'') {{transitive}} to use caution; e.g., "Beware the ides of March". --Shakespeare

====Usage Note====
Beware is a [[defective verb]] and lacks forms such as the third-person singular simple present *bewares and the simple past *bewared.

